# Cross-agent context bridge

This project is being worked on collaboratively by **Claude Code** and **Cursor**. Whichever agent finishes a turn last writes a summary of that turn to `context/last_update.md`. Read that file at the start of every response to see what the *other* agent just did.

If `agent: claude` is in the file, that's a turn you (Cursor) did NOT do — read it and reconcile before answering.
If `agent: cursor` is in the file, that's your own previous turn — you can ignore it.

The full update is here: @context/last_update.md

You should also check recent git history (`git log --oneline -5`) to see what the other agent committed.
